Actress Biodun Okeowo has declared her driver, Jamiu Abimbola, missing with her car. The actress made the declaration via her official Instagram handle on Monday. Okeowo further stressed that she neither sent her driver on an errand nor knew his whereabouts or that of her vehicle. She also said she has made a formal report with the police but noted that she has not alleged theft.   ‘How to use your ‘Bakassi’ to lure Yoruba men at parties’     I hired seven rainmakers to provoke heavy rainfall- Cubana…     Obi Cubana to youths: we rise by lifting others   Read Also: Obi Cubana to youths: we rise by lifting others - Advertisement - “I said he’s missing with my car, I’ve not concluded that he stole it. I don’t know what happened yet, I have reported it to the police,” she said. The Omoborty actress said she decided to make the declaration on her social media pages to help find the whereabouts of the driver and her vehicle. “I know with the power of social media, something can be done,” she said further. Okeowo urged fans and followers to contact her if they have any useful information